-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest
-- 
-- Sun Aug 10, 2014 11:49PM EDT
-- None



Aug 11 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* Royal Bank of Scotland Group PLC <RBS.L> is shutting its controversial turnaround division and the two most senior executives who ran it are to leave the bank, a person familiar with the situation said on Friday. [ID:nL6N0QE361] * Snapchat Inc's financing talks with China's Alibaba Group Holding Ltd <IPO-BABA.N> are over, Bloomberg reported, citing people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0QF017]  * Tango, the mobile messaging company, is arranging a financing transaction that would value its business at around $1.5 billion, roughly one-third more than the valuation it received just five months ago, according to three people familiar with the situation. [ID:nL2N0QE00P]  * Private equity giant TPG Capital Management LP [TPG.UL]  made a $3.1 billion approach for Australia's Treasury Wine Estates Ltd <TWE.AX>, a source said, setting the scene for a possible bid war for the world's No.2 winemaker with rival KKR & Co LP <KKR.N>. [ID:nL4N0QG0SX]  * Blackstone Group LP <BX.N> is close to a deal to buy a 50 percent stake worth $1.2 billion in a gas field in Louisiana currently owned by Royal Dutch Shell <RDSa.L>, according to a person familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0QG0RP]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]